Interface Individual<O,J>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - is the ontology.
    J - is the ground.
    All Superinterfaces:

    All Known Subinterfaces:

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FullIndividualDesc, IndividualGround, LinkIndividualDesc, ObjectLinkIndividualDesc, RestrictionIndividualDesc, TypeIndividualDesc, TypeIndividualDesc

    public interface Individual<O,J>
extends Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>
    This interface is a part of the core of OWLOOP architecture. It contains interfaces of the expressions that can be applied to the OWL entity OWLDataProperty (i.e., OWLNamedIndividual).

    The expressions are the following:

    • Individual.Equivalent: this expression describes an Individual same-as another Individual.
    • Individual.Disjoint: this expression describes an Individual different from another Individual.
    • Individual.Type: this expression describes the Type/s (i.e., class/es) of an Individual.
    • Individual.ObjectLink: this expression describes an ObjectProperty and Individuals related via that ObjectProperty, for an Individual.
    • Individual.DataLink: this expression describes an DataProperty and Individuals related via that DataProperty, for an Individual.
